			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Who Is nivio?</strong><br />
nivio is a hot technology startup that is leading the way in offering a full Windows desktop in the cloud.&nbsp; We are disrupting the way people interact with their computers and their files.&nbsp; In the process, we&#39;re disrupting the way business is done.&nbsp; At nivio, we believe in offering a fantastic product at a fair price that addresses a real need. nivio&#39;s desktop in the cloud is a real Windows desktop environment, with 40+ full native applications to choose from such as Microsoft Office, Skype and Evernote.&nbsp; Our service is available on any connected PC, Mac, Chromebook, Android device, iPad, iPhone and smartphone.&nbsp; Plus it comes with 10GB of free cloud storage&hellip;because that&#39;s how we roll.</p>
<p>
We offer a great working culture, with flexible working hours, support for work life balance and amazing career growth. If you&#39;re crazy smart and have a lot to offer...if you want to grow and blossom, learn new things, achieve things you thought were impossible and reach for the stars, then come work with us.</p>
<p>
nivio is headquartered in Palo Alto, California, with offices in the UK, India and Australia.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br />
As nivio&rsquo;s Senior System Administrator you will manage thousands of cloud-based Windows and/or Linux&nbsp; servers hosted in multiple data centers worldwide.&nbsp; The ideal candidate is a self-starter who is driven to improve systems and processes.&nbsp; Success in this role is defined by automating everything while having unprecedented service uptime.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Design, deploy and operate alarm and monitoring systems for a large-scale world-wide deployment of windows servers.</li>
<li>
Install, manage and configure Windows server technologies such as IIS, Active Directory, SQL server, App-V, etc.</li>
<li>
Design and deploy network based software installs and updates &ndash; managing thousands of machines automatically.</li>
<li>
Participate in 24x7 on-call support for an always-on worldwide service.</li>
<li>
Work hand-in-hand with software development team to ensure the system is designed for operability.</li>
<li>
Author scripts to automate all aspects of system deployment, monitoring and alarming.</li>
<li>
Design and implement security policies to keep data and systems safe from intrusion or denial of service.</li>
<li>
Keep the service up and always running.&nbsp; Our users require 24x7 access!</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Minimum 5 years industry experience.</li>
<li>
Intimate knowledge of Windows Server technologies including Windows Server 2008, Active Directory, SQL Server, SCOM, App-V and more.</li>
<li>
Demonstrated ability to write scripts and use automated tools to manage large-scale deployments.</li>
<li>
Experience with virtual machine environments: one or more of EC2, Rackspace, VMware or others.</li>
<li>
Detailed knowledge of TCP/IP networks: routing, firewalls, DNS, load balancing and redundancy, etc.</li>
<li>
Direct experience in large-scale internet facing hosted computing environment managing hundreds of machines or more</li>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in computer science, information technology or equivalent.</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
This role will be based out of our office in Palo Alto, CA.&nbsp;&nbsp; nivio offers an attractive compensation plan with competitive salary, performance based bonuses and a good benefits package.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
This position reports to the Director of System Operations.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
